{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Wkv51diDkQd9LLTjuhjrne","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.HashMap;\n     4→import java.util.Map;\n     5→import javax.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     6→import javax.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     7→import org.glassfish.jersey.server.ServerProperties;\n     8→\n     9→/** Jakarta REST configuration. */\n    10→@ApplicationPath(\"rest\")\n    11→public class RestConfiguration extends Application {\n    12→\n    13→  @Override\n    14→  public Map<String, Object> getProperties() {\n    15→    Map<String, Object> properties = new HashMap<String, Object>();\n    16→    properties.put(ServerProperties.BV_SEND_ERROR_IN_RESPONSE, true);\n    17→    return properties;\n    18→  }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LxRZPsJwQVEk7jGF5wP2c6","session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"2121eddb-7f62-418d-83dd-b2e60581a293"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-3-5-haiku-20241022","id":"msg_bdrk_01B28d6RfLodgXZbAx7ueSdC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_012HyU8ZHifEzSXcx49qC58x","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/BookingService.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":545,"cache_read_input_tokens":28975,"output_tokens":262},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LxRZPsJwQVEk7jGF5wP2c6","session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"f87d9630-e2c8-49b7-b38f-89c6fe17dfb1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012HyU8ZHifEzSXcx49qC58x","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import javax.validation.Valid;\n     6→import javax.validation.constraints.Future;\n     7→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    11→\n    12→/** Cargo booking service. */\n    13→public interface BookingService {\n    14→\n    15→  /** Registers a new cargo in the tracking system, not yet routed. */\n    16→  TrackingId bookNewCargo(\n    17→      @NotNull(message = \"Origin is required.\") @Valid UnLocode origin,\n    18→      @NotNull(message = \"Destination is required.\") @Valid UnLocode destination,\n    19→      @NotNull(message = \"Deadline is required.\")\n    20→          @Future(message = \"Deadline must be in the future.\")\n    21→          LocalDate arrivalDeadline);\n    22→\n    23→  /**\n    24→   * Requests a list of itineraries describing possible routes for this cargo.\n    25→   *\n    26→   * @param trackingId Cargo tracking ID\n    27→   * @return A list of possible itineraries for this cargo\n    28→   */\n    29→  List<Itinerary> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(\n    30→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId);\n    31→\n    32→  void assignCargoToRoute(\n    33→      @NotNull(message = \"Itinerary is required.\") @Valid Itinerary itinerary,\n    34→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId);\n    35→\n    36→  void changeDestination(\n    37→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId,\n    38→      @NotNull(message = \"Destination is required.\") @Valid UnLocode unLocode);\n    39→\n    40→  void changeDeadline(\n    41→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId,\n    42→      @NotNull(message = \"Deadline is required.\")\n    43→          @Future(message = \"Deadline must be in the future.\")\n    44→          LocalDate deadline);\n    45→}\n    46→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LxRZPsJwQVEk7jGF5wP2c6","session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"add11c8b-1f4d-41be-9bb8-8c5a9432a88c"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-3-5-haiku-20241022","id":"msg_bdrk_014to5qWQhtXMSko73UAPdrX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01QaVChcJoBEgSzrpEoz2w98","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultBookingService.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1040,"cache_read_input_tokens":29520,"output_tokens":127},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LxRZPsJwQVEk7jGF5wP2c6","session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"634870da-e6ab-40b9-8fc1-cf78edd2f1a7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QaVChcJoBEgSzrpEoz2w98","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.Collections;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     7→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     8→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n     9→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.BookingService;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service.RoutingService;\n    20→\n    21→@Stateless\n    22→public class DefaultBookingService implements BookingService {\n    23→\n    24→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    25→  @Inject private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    26→  @Inject private RoutingService routingService;\n    27→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    28→\n    29→  @Override\n    30→  public TrackingId bookNewCargo(\n    31→      UnLocode originUnLocode, UnLocode destinationUnLocode, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    32→    TrackingId trackingId = cargoRepository.nextTrackingId();\n    33→    Location origin = locationRepository.find(originUnLocode);\n    34→    Location destination = locationRepository.find(destinationUnLocode);\n    35→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    36→        new RouteSpecification(origin, destination, arrivalDeadline);\n    37→\n    38→    Cargo cargo = new Cargo(trackingId, routeSpecification);\n    39→\n    40→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    41→    logger.log(\n    42→        Level.INFO, \"Booked new cargo with tracking ID {0}\", cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString());\n    43→\n    44→    return cargo.getTrackingId();\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  @Override\n    48→  public List<Itinerary> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(TrackingId trackingId) {\n    49→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    50→\n    51→    if (cargo == null) {\n    52→      return Collections.emptyList();\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    return routingService.fetchRoutesForSpecification(cargo.getRouteSpecification());\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  @Override\n    59→  public void assignCargoToRoute(Itinerary itinerary, TrackingId trackingId) {\n    60→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    61→\n    62→    cargo.assignToRoute(itinerary);\n    63→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    64→\n    65→    logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Assigned cargo {0} to new route\", trackingId);\n    66→  }\n    67→\n    68→  @Override\n    69→  public void changeDestination(TrackingId trackingId, UnLocode unLocode) {\n    70→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    71→    Location newDestination = locationRepository.find(unLocode);\n    72→\n    73→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    74→        new RouteSpecification(\n    75→            cargo.getOrigin(), newDestination, cargo.getRouteSpecification().getArrivalDeadline());\n    76→    cargo.specifyNewRoute(routeSpecification);\n    77→\n    78→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    79→\n    80→    logger.log(\n    81→        Level.INFO,\n    82→        \"Changed destination for cargo {0} to {1}\",\n    83→        new Object[] {trackingId, routeSpecification.getDestination()});\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  @Override\n    87→  public void changeDeadline(TrackingId trackingId, LocalDate newDeadline) {\n    88→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    89→\n    90→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    91→        new RouteSpecification(\n    92→            cargo.getOrigin(), cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination(), newDeadline);\n    93→    cargo.specifyNewRoute(routeSpecification);\n    94→\n    95→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    96→\n    97→    logger.log(\n    98→        Level.INFO,\n    99→        \"Changed deadline for cargo {0} to {1}\",\n   100→        new Object[] {trackingId, newDeadline});\n   101→  }\n   102→}\n   103→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LxRZPsJwQVEk7jGF5wP2c6","session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"9706e2f6-cacf-4134-8d1d-58e99aa952c8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01LxRZPsJwQVEk7jGF5wP2c6","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"8. Infrastructure Package Files\nKey files:\n- CargoUpdated.java in events/cdi/\n- LoggerProducer.java\n- Various JMS and JPA implementations\n\n9. Domain Package Files\nKey files in various subpackages (cargo, handling, location, voyage, shared):\n- Cargo.java\n- CargoRepository.java\n- HandlingEvent.java\n- Location.java\n- Voyage.java\n- Various specification and utility classes\n\n10. XHTML Files Path\nI'll list all the XHTML file paths I found earlier:\n\nWEB-INF Templates:\n- /src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/templates/common/public.xhtml\n\nAdmin Pages:\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/about.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/dashboard.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/dialogs/change_arrival_deadline.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/dialogs/change_destination.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/route.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/selectItinerary.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/show.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/tables/list_claimed.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/tables/list_not_routed.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/tables/list_routed.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/tracking/map.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/tracking/mapFrame.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/admin/tracking/track.xhtml\n\nBooking Pages:\n- /src/main/webapp/booking/booking-date.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/booking/booking-destination.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/booking/booking.xhtml\n\nOther Pages:\n- /src/main/webapp/event-logger/index.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/index.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/public/about.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/public/mapFrame.xhtml\n- /src/main/webapp/public/track.xhtml\n\nWould you like me to read any specific files in full detail, or is this overview sufficient for your migration planning?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"be96aeb9-3b2b-41b1-b8ff-2b8cc692b37f"}
