{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NmqQyH8si8ZBCoNoeXXL5S","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<web-app xmlns=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee\"\n     3→  xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" version=\"4.0\"\n     4→  xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee https://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee/web-app_4_0.xsd\">\n     5→  <!-- Overriding system level defaults is a decent usage of XML. -->\n     6→  <context-param>\n     7→    <param-name>javax.faces.PROJECT_STAGE</param-name>\n     8→    <param-value>Development</param-value>\n     9→  </context-param>\n    10→  <context-param>\n    11→    <param-name>javax.faces.CLIENT_WINDOW_MODE</param-name>\n    12→    <param-value>url</param-value>\n    13→  </context-param>\n    14→  <context-param>\n    15→    <param-name>primefaces.THEME</param-name>\n    16→    <param-value>saga</param-value>\n    17→  </context-param>\n    18→  <context-param>\n    19→    <param-name>primefaces.FONT_AWESOME</param-name>\n    20→    <param-value>true</param-value>\n    21→  </context-param>\n    22→  <context-param>\n    23→    <param-name>primefaces.MOVE_SCRIPTS_TO_BOTTOM</param-name>\n    24→    <param-value>true</param-value>\n    25→  </context-param>\n    26→  <mime-mapping>\n    27→    <extension>ttf</extension>\n    28→    <mime-type>application/font-sfnt</mime-type>\n    29→  </mime-mapping>\n    30→  <mime-mapping>\n    31→    <extension>woff</extension>\n    32→    <mime-type>application/font-woff</mime-type>\n    33→  </mime-mapping>\n    34→  <mime-mapping>\n    35→    <extension>woff2</extension>\n    36→    <mime-type>application/font-woff2</mime-type>\n    37→  </mime-mapping>\n    38→  <mime-mapping>\n    39→    <extension>eot</extension>\n    40→    <mime-type>application/vnd.ms-fontobject</mime-type>\n    41→  </mime-mapping>\n    42→  <servlet>\n    43→    <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    44→    <servlet-class>javax.faces.webapp.FacesServlet</servlet-class>\n    45→    <load-on-startup>1</load-on-startup>\n    46→  </servlet>\n    47→  <servlet-mapping>\n    48→    <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    49→    <url-pattern>*.xhtml</url-pattern>\n    50→  </servlet-mapping>\n    51→  <welcome-file-list>\n    52→    <welcome-file>index.xhtml</welcome-file>\n    53→    <welcome-file>index.html</welcome-file>\n    54→  </welcome-file-list>\n    55→  <!-- Application resource dependencies like JMS queues and data sources are still\n    56→    good candidates for XML, as is application configuration. -->\n    57→  <env-entry>\n    58→    <env-entry-name>java:app/configuration/GraphTraversalUrl</env-entry-name>\n    59→    <env-entry-type>java.lang.String</env-entry-type>\n    60→    <env-entry-value>${webapp.graphTraversalUrl}</env-entry-value>\n    61→  </env-entry>\n    62→  <!-- Defining these at the application server level instead of here can be more\n    63→    operations friendly and help make deployment even faster. -->\n    64→  <data-source>\n    65→    <name>java:app/jdbc/CargoTrackerDatabase</name>\n    66→    <class-name>${db.driverClass}</class-name>\n    67→    <url>${db.jdbcUrl}</url>\n    68→    <user>${db.user}</user>\n    69→    <password>${db.password}</password>\n    70→    <max-pool-size>32</max-pool-size>\n    71→    <min-pool-size>2</min-pool-size>\n    72→  </data-source>\n    73→  <jms-destination>\n    74→    <name>java:app/jms/CargoHandledQueue</name>\n    75→    <interface-name>javax.jms.Queue</interface-name>\n    76→    <destination-name>CargoHandledQueue</destination-name>\n    77→  </jms-destination>\n    78→  <jms-destination>\n    79→    <name>java:app/jms/MisdirectedCargoQueue</name>\n    80→    <interface-name>javax.jms.Queue</interface-name>\n    81→    <destination-name>MisdirectedCargoQueue</destination-name>\n    82→  </jms-destination>\n    83→  <jms-destination>\n    84→    <name>java:app/jms/DeliveredCargoQueue</name>\n    85→    <interface-name>javax.jms.Queue</interface-name>\n    86→    <destination-name>DeliveredCargoQueue</destination-name>\n    87→  </jms-destination>\n    88→  <jms-destination>\n    89→    <name>java:app/jms/RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue</name>\n    90→    <interface-name>javax.jms.Queue</interface-name>\n    91→    <destination-name>RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue</destination-name>\n    92→  </jms-destination>\n    93→  <jms-destination>\n    94→    <name>java:app/jms/HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue</name>\n    95→    <interface-name>javax.jms.Queue</interface-name>\n    96→    <destination-name>HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue</destination-name>\n    97→  </jms-destination>\n    98→</web-app>\n    99→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X7n2JiX4wVDwJSQHwz6pWY","session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"a9264f3e-bca7-4caf-905c-a48a901f0434"}
