{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DWh9wps9JkJ3UnMc7Awdno","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     4→<h:head>\n     5→  <title>Change Destination</title>\n     6→</h:head>\n     7→<body>\n     8→  <f:metadata>\n     9→    <f:viewParam name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{changeDestination.trackingId}\" />\n    10→    <f:viewAction action=\"#{changeDestination.load}\" />\n    11→  </f:metadata>\n    12→\n    13→  <div class=\"ui-g full-page\">\n    14→    <h:form>\n    15→      <h:panelGrid columns=\"2\" cellpadding=\"15\">\n    16→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Origin:\" />\n    17→        <p:outputLabel value=\"#{changeDestination.cargo.originName}\" />\n    18→\n    19→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Current destination: \" />\n    20→        <p:outputLabel value=\"#{changeDestination.cargo.finalDestinationName}\" />\n    21→\n    22→        <p:outputLabel value=\"New destination: \" />\n    23→        <p:selectOneMenu value=\"#{changeDestination.destinationUnlocode}\"\n    24→          p:autofocus=\"true\">\n    25→          <f:selectItems value=\"#{changeDestination.potentialDestinations}\"\n    26→            var=\"location\" itemLabel=\"#{location.name}\"\n    27→            itemValue=\"#{location.unLocode}\" />\n    28→        </p:selectOneMenu>\n    29→\n    30→        <p:commandButton value=\"Cancel\"\n    31→          action=\"#{changeDestinationDialog.cancel()}\" />\n    32→\n    33→\n    34→        <p:commandButton value=\"Update\"\n    35→          action=\"#{changeDestination.changeDestination()}\"\n    36→          oncomplete=\"window.location.replace(window.location.href);\" />\n    37→      </h:panelGrid>\n    38→    </h:form>\n    39→  </div>\n    40→</body>\n    41→</html>\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X7n2JiX4wVDwJSQHwz6pWY","session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"2a8dd16d-63d3-4a51-bd0f-be965ba0edcc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Ff9UVf3JnATifHQxgPya21","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     4→<h:head>\n     5→  <title>Change Deadline</title>\n     6→</h:head>\n     7→<body>\n     8→  <f:metadata>\n     9→    <f:viewParam name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.trackingId}\" />\n    10→    <f:viewAction action=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.load}\" />\n    11→  </f:metadata>\n    12→\n    13→  <div class=\"ui-g full-page\">\n    14→    <h:form>\n    15→      <h:panelGrid columns=\"2\" cellpadding=\"15\">\n    16→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Origin:\" />\n    17→        <p:outputLabel value=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.cargo.originName}\" />\n    18→\n    19→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Destination: \" />\n    20→        <p:outputLabel\n    21→          value=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.cargo.finalDestinationName}\" />\n    22→\n    23→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Deadline: \" />\n    24→        <p:datePicker value=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.arrivalDeadline}\" />\n    25→\n    26→        <p:commandButton value=\"Cancel\"\n    27→          action=\"#{changeArrivalDeadlineDialog.cancel()}\" />\n    28→\n    29→        <p:commandButton value=\"Update\"\n    30→          action=\"#{changeArrivalDeadline.changeArrivalDeadline()}\"\n    31→          oncomplete=\"window.location.replace(window.location.href);\" />\n    32→      </h:panelGrid>\n    33→    </h:form>\n    34→  </div>\n    35→</body>\n    36→</html>\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X7n2JiX4wVDwJSQHwz6pWY","session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"872dc26d-6f5a-48b9-9d81-85fc6466f577"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01P6ZZuvzYnhc5J9VQoduPNL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n     3→        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n     4→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     5→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     6→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\"\n     7→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     8→<h:head>\n     9→  <title><ui:insert name=\"title\">Title</ui:insert></title>\n    10→\n    11→  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" />\n    12→  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n    13→\n    14→  <h:outputStylesheet name=\"css/app.css\" />\n    15→\n    16→  <link rel=\"stylesheet\"\n    17→    href=\"//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.3.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\" />\n    18→</h:head>\n    19→\n    20→<h:body>\n    21→  <div class=\"ui-g full-page\">\n    22→    <!-- MENU -->\n    23→    <div class=\"ui-g-12 ui-md-2 side-panel\">\n    24→      <div class=\"ui-g-12 menu-container\">\n    25→        <h:form>\n    26→          <h:graphicImage value=\"#{resource['/images/CTlogobadge128.png']}\"\n    27→            class=\"side-panel-img\" alt=\"Cargo Tracker logo badge\" />\n    28→          <p:menu>\n    29→            <p:menuitem value=\"Tracking\"\n    30→              url=\"#{request.contextPath}/public/track.xhtml\" />\n    31→            <p:menuitem value=\"About\"\n    32→              url=\"#{request.contextPath}/public/about.xhtml\" />\n    33→          </p:menu>\n    34→        </h:form>\n    35→      </div>\n    36→    </div>\n    37→\n    38→    <!-- Main Section -->\n    39→    <div class=\"ui-g-12 ui-md-10 ui-g-nopad\">\n    40→      <div class=\"ui-g-12 ui-g-nopad\">\n    41→        <div class=\"ui-g\">\n    42→          <ui:insert name=\"content\">Default Content</ui:insert>\n    43→        </div>\n    44→      </div>\n    45→    </div>\n    46→  </div>\n    47→</h:body>\n    48→</html>\n    49→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X7n2JiX4wVDwJSQHwz6pWY","session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"057e62cb-a7e3-474e-8a6f-385bd08d2196"}
