*\n36-42. Voyage entities including Voyage, VoyageNumber, Schedule, CarrierMovement, SampleVoyages, and VoyageRepository\n\n#### **Domain Shared (6 files)**\n43-48. Specification pattern implementations and utilities\n\n#### **Domain Service (1 file)**\n49. RoutingService interface\n\n#### **Infrastructure - Persistence (4 files)**\n50-53. JPA repository implementations for Cargo, Location, Voyage, and HandlingEvent\n\n#### **Infrastructure - Routing (1 file)**\n54. ExternalRoutingService - @Stateless service calling external routing API\n\n#### **Infrastructure - Logging (1 file)**\n55. LoggerProducer - CDI producer for Logger\n\n#### **Infrastructure - Messaging (6 files)**\n56-61. JMS-based event consumers and producers\n\n#### **Infrastructure - Events (1 file)**\n62. CargoUpdated CDI qualifier\n\n#### **Interfaces - General (4 files)**\n63-66. FacesConfiguration, CoordinatesFactory, Coordinates\n\n#### **Interfaces - Booking Facade (11 files)**\n67-77. Booking service facade, DTOs, and assemblers\n\n#### **Interfaces - Booking Web (10 files)**\n78-87. JSF backing beans for booking UI\n\n#### **Interfaces - Booking SSE (3 files)**\n88-90. Server-Sent Events for real-time tracking\n\n#### **Interfaces - Handling (2 files)**\n91-92. HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt and file processing components\n\n#### **Interfaces - Handling File (7 files)**\n93-99. Batch processing components for file-based event registration\n\n#### **Interfaces - Tracking Web (2 files)**\n100-101. Public tracking interface backing beans\n\n#### **Pathfinder API (4 files)**\n102-105. Graph traversal service and transit path DTOs\n\n### Key Findings:\n\n**Jakarta EE Technologies Used:**\n- **EJB**: @Stateless, @Singleton, @Startup, @MessageDriven\n- **JPA**: @Entity, @Embeddable, @ManyToOne, @PersistenceContext\n- **CDI**: @Inject, @ApplicationScoped, @RequestScoped, @ViewScoped, @Named\n- **JMS**: JMSContext, @Resource for destinations\n- **JAX-RS**: @Path, @GET, @Produces, @QueryParam\n- **Faces**: @FacesConfig, @FlowScoped\n- **Batch**: AbstractItemReader, AbstractItemWriter, JobListener\n- **Validation**: @NotNull, @Valid, @Pattern, @Size, @NotEmpty\n\n**Architecture Pattern**: Domain-Driven Design (DDD) with clear separation:\n- Domain model (entities, value objects, aggregates)\n- Application services\n- Infrastructure (persistence, messaging, routing)\n- Interfaces (web, REST, batch)\n\nAll 104 files have been successfully read and their complete contents are available for your migration planning."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"4188a8d4-b4d4-499f-b954-9a3fdef5bdd7"}
