{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01ByP8BPDnrCWVkBS8129Vjr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_019nPqwv6u5Ri7BCdKG7L648","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Refactor interfaces package","prompt":"I need to refactor all Java files in the interfaces package from Jakarta EE 8 to Quarkus. The files are at:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/\n\nThis package contains JSF backing beans, booking facade, SSE service, handling event classes, and batch processing classes. Quarkus doesn't support JSF, so we need to convert JSF backing beans to REST endpoints. Here are the specific changes needed:\n\n### 1. FacesConfiguration.java - DELETE or empty this file completely. Replace with empty placeholder:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n\n// JSF configuration removed for Quarkus migration\n// Faces/JSF is not supported in Quarkus\n```\n\n### 2. Coordinates.java and CoordinatesFactory.java - Read them and just update javax.* to jakarta.* imports if any. These are utility classes.\n\n### 3. booking/facade/BookingServiceFacade.java - Interface, update javax.* to jakarta.* if any.\n\n### 4. booking/facade/dto/*.java - DTOs (CargoRoute, CargoStatus, Leg, Location, RouteCandidate, TrackingEvents) - update javax.* to jakarta.* if any.\n\n### 5. booking/facade/internal/DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java - Update:\n- `javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped` → `jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped`\n- `javax.inject.Inject` → `jakarta.inject.Inject`\n\n### 6. booking/facade/internal/assembler/*.java (5 assembler files) - Update javax.* to jakarta.* if any. Read each, apply changes.\n\n### 7. booking/web/*.java - These are JSF backing beans. They need to be converted to REST resources OR removed and replaced. For this migration, we'll REMOVE the JSF-specific annotations and convert key functionality to REST endpoints. Specifically:\n\n**Booking.java** - Remove JSF dependencies. Rewrite:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport java.time.LocalDate;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n\n/**\n * Booking service - converted from JSF backing bean to CDI bean.\n * Functionality exposed via BookingRestService REST endpoint.\n */\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class Booking implements Serializable {\n  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public List<Location> getLocations() {\n    return bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n  }\n\n  public String register(String originUnlocode, String destinationUnlocode, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    if (!originUnlocode.equals(destinationUnlocode)) {\n      return bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(originUnlocode, destinationUnlocode, arrivalDeadline);\n    }\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**ListCargo.java** - Rewrite:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class ListCargo {\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public List<CargoRoute> getCargos() {\n    return bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**CargoDetails.java** - Read and rewrite without JSF:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class CargoDetails {\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public CargoRoute getCargo(String trackingId) {\n    return bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Track.java (in booking/web/)** - Read and rewrite without JSF:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class Track {\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public CargoStatus getCargoStatus(String trackingId) {\n    return bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(trackingId);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**ChangeDestination.java, ChangeDestinationDialog.java, ChangeArrivalDeadline.java, ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java, ItinerarySelection.java** - Read each and simplify to remove JSF. Replace each with a minimal CDI bean:\n\nFor example, ChangeDestination.java:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class ChangeDestination {\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public void changeDestination(String trackingId, String destinationUnlocode) {\n    bookingServiceFacade.changeDestination(trackingId, destinationUnlocode);\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSimilar minimal patterns for the others. Read the existing file first to understand the logic, then rewrite.\n\n### 8. booking/sse/RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java - Rewrite for Quarkus REST SSE:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.event.ObservesAsync;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\nimport org.jboss.resteasy.reactive.RestStreamElementType;\nimport io.smallrye.mutiny.Multi;\nimport io.smallrye.mutiny.operators.multi.processors.BroadcastProcessor;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@Path(\"/rest/cargo\")\npublic class RealtimeCargoTrackingService {\n  @Inject private Logger logger;\n  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n\n  private final BroadcastProcessor<RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter> processor = BroadcastProcessor.create();\n\n  @GET\n  @Produces(MediaType.SERVER_SENT_EVENTS)\n  @RestStreamElementType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n  public Multi<RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter> tracking() {\n    // First emit all current cargo, then stream updates\n    Multi<RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter> existing = Multi.createFrom().iterable(\n        cargoRepository.findAll().stream()\n            .map(RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter::new)\n            .toList());\n    return Multi.createBy().concatenating().streams(existing, processor);\n  }\n\n  public void onCargoUpdated(@ObservesAsync @CargoUpdated Cargo cargo) {\n    logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE event broadcast for cargo: {0}\", cargo);\n    processor.onNext(new RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter(cargo));\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 9. booking/sse/RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter.java, LocationViewAdapter.java - Read and update javax.* to jakarta.* if any.\n\n### 10. handling/HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt.java - No javax imports, no change needed. Already read.\n\n### 11. handling/file/*.java (batch files) - These use Jakarta Batch API. For Quarkus, we'll convert them:\n\n**UploadDirectoryScanner.java** - Rewrite using Quarkus @Scheduled:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class UploadDirectoryScanner {\n  @Inject private Logger logger;\n\n  @Scheduled(every = \"120s\")\n  public void processFiles() {\n    logger.info(\"Scheduled file processing check (batch job replacement).\");\n    // Batch processing placeholder - in Quarkus we would use a different approach\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**EventFilesCheckpoint.java, EventItemReader.java, EventItemWriter.java, EventLineParseException.java, FileProcessorJobListener.java, LineParseExceptionListener.java** - Read each and update javax.* to jakarta.*, removing any batch-specific annotations/extends that won't work in Quarkus. Replace batch API references with simple class stubs.\n\nFor EventItemReader.java - it probably extends AbstractItemReader. Rewrite as a simple class:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n\n// Batch processing item reader - converted from Jakarta Batch to stub for Quarkus\n@Dependent\npublic class EventItemReader implements Serializable {\n  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n  // Batch processing is not directly supported in Quarkus\n  // This would need to be replaced with a Quarkus-compatible approach\n}\n```\n\nSimilar stubs for EventItemWriter.java and the listener classes.\n\n### 12. tracking/web/Track.java - Read and rewrite without JSF:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.tracking.web;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class Track {\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public CargoStatus getCargoStatus(String trackingId) {\n    return bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(trackingId);\n  }\n}\n```\n\nPlease read EVERY Java file in the interfaces/ directory tree, apply the appropriate changes, and write them all back. Make sure to handle ALL files.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":532,"cache_read_input_tokens":102446,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":532,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3049},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"1429009b-9d8a-4d3f-b7db-c9793f1e1c31"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to refactor all Java files in the interfaces package from Jakarta EE 8 to Quarkus. The files are at:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/\n\nThis package contains JSF backing beans, booking facade, SSE service, handling event classes, and batch processing classes. Quarkus doesn't support JSF, so we need to convert JSF backing beans to REST endpoints. Here are the specific changes needed:\n\n### 1. FacesConfiguration.java - DELETE or empty this file completely. Replace with empty placeholder:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n\n// JSF configuration removed for Quarkus migration\n// Faces/JSF is not supported in Quarkus\n```\n\n### 2. Coordinates.java and CoordinatesFactory.java - Read them and just update javax.* to jakarta.* imports if any. These are utility classes.\n\n### 3. booking/facade/BookingServiceFacade.java - Interface, update javax.* to jakarta.* if any.\n\n### 4. booking/facade/dto/*.java - DTOs (CargoRoute, CargoStatus, Leg, Location, RouteCandidate, TrackingEvents) - update javax.* to jakarta.* if any.\n\n### 5. booking/facade/internal/DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java - Update:\n- `javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped` → `jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped`\n- `javax.inject.Inject` → `jakarta.inject.Inject`\n\n### 6. booking/facade/internal/assembler/*.java (5 assembler files) - Update javax.* to jakarta.* if any. Read each, apply changes.\n\n### 7. booking/web/*.java - These are JSF backing beans. They need to be converted to REST resources OR removed and replaced. For this migration, we'll REMOVE the JSF-specific annotations and convert key functionality to REST endpoints. Specifically:\n\n**Booking.java** - Remove JSF dependencies. Rewrite:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport java.time.LocalDate;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n\n/**\n * Booking service - converted from JSF backing bean to CDI bean.\n * Functionality exposed via BookingRestService REST endpoint.\n */\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class Booking implements Serializable {\n  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public List<Location> getLocations() {\n    return bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n  }\n\n  public String register(String originUnlocode, String destinationUnlocode, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    if (!originUnlocode.equals(destinationUnlocode)) {\n      return bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(originUnlocode, destinationUnlocode, arrivalDeadline);\n    }\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**ListCargo.java** - Rewrite:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport java.util.List;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class ListCargo {\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public List<CargoRoute> getCargos() {\n    return bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**CargoDetails.java** - Read and rewrite without JSF:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class CargoDetails {\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public CargoRoute getCargo(String trackingId) {\n    return bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Track.java (in booking/web/)** - Read and rewrite without JSF:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class Track {\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public CargoStatus getCargoStatus(String trackingId) {\n    return bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(trackingId);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**ChangeDestination.java, ChangeDestinationDialog.java, ChangeArrivalDeadline.java, ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java, ItinerarySelection.java** - Read each and simplify to remove JSF. Replace each with a minimal CDI bean:\n\nFor example, ChangeDestination.java:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class ChangeDestination {\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public void changeDestination(String trackingId, String destinationUnlocode) {\n    bookingServiceFacade.changeDestination(trackingId, destinationUnlocode);\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSimilar minimal patterns for the others. Read the existing file first to understand the logic, then rewrite.\n\n### 8. booking/sse/RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java - Rewrite for Quarkus REST SSE:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.event.ObservesAsync;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\nimport org.jboss.resteasy.reactive.RestStreamElementType;\nimport io.smallrye.mutiny.Multi;\nimport io.smallrye.mutiny.operators.multi.processors.BroadcastProcessor;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@Path(\"/rest/cargo\")\npublic class RealtimeCargoTrackingService {\n  @Inject private Logger logger;\n  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n\n  private final BroadcastProcessor<RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter> processor = BroadcastProcessor.create();\n\n  @GET\n  @Produces(MediaType.SERVER_SENT_EVENTS)\n  @RestStreamElementType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n  public Multi<RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter> tracking() {\n    // First emit all current cargo, then stream updates\n    Multi<RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter> existing = Multi.createFrom().iterable(\n        cargoRepository.findAll().stream()\n            .map(RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter::new)\n            .toList());\n    return Multi.createBy().concatenating().streams(existing, processor);\n  }\n\n  public void onCargoUpdated(@ObservesAsync @CargoUpdated Cargo cargo) {\n    logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE event broadcast for cargo: {0}\", cargo);\n    processor.onNext(new RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter(cargo));\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 9. booking/sse/RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter.java, LocationViewAdapter.java - Read and update javax.* to jakarta.* if any.\n\n### 10. handling/HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt.java - No javax imports, no change needed. Already read.\n\n### 11. handling/file/*.java (batch files) - These use Jakarta Batch API. For Quarkus, we'll convert them:\n\n**UploadDirectoryScanner.java** - Rewrite using Quarkus @Scheduled:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class UploadDirectoryScanner {\n  @Inject private Logger logger;\n\n  @Scheduled(every = \"120s\")\n  public void processFiles() {\n    logger.info(\"Scheduled file processing check (batch job replacement).\");\n    // Batch processing placeholder - in Quarkus we would use a different approach\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**EventFilesCheckpoint.java, EventItemReader.java, EventItemWriter.java, EventLineParseException.java, FileProcessorJobListener.java, LineParseExceptionListener.java** - Read each and update javax.* to jakarta.*, removing any batch-specific annotations/extends that won't work in Quarkus. Replace batch API references with simple class stubs.\n\nFor EventItemReader.java - it probably extends AbstractItemReader. Rewrite as a simple class:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n\n// Batch processing item reader - converted from Jakarta Batch to stub for Quarkus\n@Dependent\npublic class EventItemReader implements Serializable {\n  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n  // Batch processing is not directly supported in Quarkus\n  // This would need to be replaced with a Quarkus-compatible approach\n}\n```\n\nSimilar stubs for EventItemWriter.java and the listener classes.\n\n### 12. tracking/web/Track.java - Read and rewrite without JSF:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.tracking.web;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\npublic class Track {\n  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n  public CargoStatus getCargoStatus(String trackingId) {\n    return bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(trackingId);\n  }\n}\n```\n\nPlease read EVERY Java file in the interfaces/ directory tree, apply the appropriate changes, and write them all back. Make sure to handle ALL files."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019nPqwv6u5Ri7BCdKG7L648","session_id":"a4072757-006a-493f-88e0-08a9064c7917","uuid":"855474f5-cfe6-40ad-b10e-6a0a2146ba15"}
